Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS) has confirmed an exclusive report by Tribune Online of a fire incident at its headquarters on Saturday evening. According to a statement from Head, Communications and Servicom Department, Wahab Gbadamosi, the fire occurred at the store of the headquarters annexe 1 at around 5:10 PM on Saturday. The fire affected the store by the FIRS canteen where disused/old computers awaiting disposal are often kept. ALSO READ: VIDEO: Fire guts FIRS headquarters Court sentences two to death in Ekiti Gunmen abduct police, one other in Abuja Court fixes Dec. 18 to hear N100m suit filed against CCECC… Lawmaker calls for establishment of Federal Polytechnic in… He explained that envelopes, printing paper and stationeries were destroyed in the incident. “Officials of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Fire Service arrived the scene a couple of minutes after the fire began and worked with Security and Safety officers of the FIRS, to put out the fire within two hours. “Executive Chairman, FIRS, Mr Tunde Fowler, visited the scene of the fire incident for a first-hand assessment. “Officials of the FCT Fire Service Department visited the scene again on Monday to ascertain the cause of the fire incident. “The Fire Service Department is continuing with the investigation to ascertain the cause of the fire incident.” SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
